              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3080956976679932723">The story was quite slow, and I didn&apos;t feel like the world was sufficiently fleshed out. It was mainly a few made up animals and foods that was supposed to illustrate the fact that this story is set in a different world. It is possible that if I read all the books the author wrote in this world, I &apos;get it&apos; more, but ideally you are &apos;in&apos; after only one book.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t feel like I am being entirely fair, as I read this not long after reading The Lord of the Rings, and that comparison is hardly fair a</span>
  <span id="freeText3080956976679932723" style="display:none">The story was quite slow, and I didn't feel like the world was sufficiently fleshed out. It was mainly a few made up animals and foods that was supposed to illustrate the fact that this story is set in a different world. It is possible that if I read all the books the author wrote in this world, I 'get it' more, but ideally you are 'in' after only one book.<br /><br />I don't feel like I am being entirely fair, as I read this not long after reading The Lord of the Rings, and that comparison is hardly fair at all.<br /><br />I enjoyed reading it but it's not the kind of book I will be reading again. Once you've read it you got everything there is to get, and I don't feel like there are hidden treasures or additional value to be gotten from reading it again. The story line is a bit too boring to want to read it for the story's sake alone.</span>
